# Design System & Typography Guidelines

## Color System
- Follow the color system defined in [tailwind.config.js](mdc:tailwind.config.js)
- Use HSL color variables for consistency: `hsl(var(--primary))`, `hsl(var(--secondary))`, etc.
- Maintain sufficient contrast ratios for accessibility (WCAG AA minimum)
- Support both light and dark modes with appropriate color schemes

## Typography Scale
- Use the typography scale defined in MDXComponents for consistent sizing
- Heading hierarchy: h1 (text-4xl), h2 (text-3xl), h3 (text-2xl), h4 (text-xl)
- Body text: Base size for optimal readability
- Maintain proper line height for readability: 1.5-1.7 for body, 1.2-1.3 for headings

## Spacing System
- Use consistent spacing based on the Tailwind scale
- Create visual hierarchy through intentional spacing
- Maintain proper whitespace around content sections
- Ensure breathing room between elements

## Border & Shadow System
- Use consistent border radius: lg, md, sm as defined in tailwind.config.js
- Apply shadows thoughtfully to create depth when needed
- Maintain border styles for UI elements requiring boundaries
- Ensure borders have sufficient contrast against backgrounds

## Design Language
- Aim for simplicity and minimalism in visual design
- Use whitespace strategically to create focus and hierarchy
- Maintain visual consistency across all components
- Create a cohesive look and feel that reflects your personal brand

## Implementation Details
- Use Tailwind's typography plugin for richly formatted content
- Leverage CSS variables for theme customization
- Override default markdown elements in MDXComponents.tsx
- Tailor shadcn/ui components to match your design system